      <h2 class="teal">Patient Protection and Affordable Care Act (Obamacare)</h2><br>
      
      <p>The Affordable Care Act is a federal statute signed into law in 2010 that introduces a sweeping overhaul of the nation&#39;s healthcare system. The act grants the federal government significant regulatory powers and price controls over U.S. medical service providers and insurance companies.</p><br>
      
