      <h2 class="teal">Vaccinations</h2><br>
      
      <p>Vaccines are medications, usually in the form of shots, that can be taken by a patient in order to prevent diseases. Some of the most common vaccinations are ones for the flu, measles, mumps, polio, human papilloma virus (HPV), chickenpox, shingles, tuberculosis, whooping cough, and meningococcal. </p><br>
      
