      <h2 class="teal">What does this mean to me?</h2><br>
      
      <p>If you are trying to figure out what kind of health care system you feel that we should have in our country, try asking yourself the following questions:</p><br>
      
      <ul>
         <li>What kind of health care needs do I have?&nbsp;Do I have any pre-existing conditions that I would want to make sure are covered by most health plans, or my health plan at the very least? Do I deserve to be charged more for a condition that I was born with or otherwise did not ask to have?</li>
         <li>What kind of health care needs does my family or loved ones have?&nbsp;Health care plans often involve the whole family, so you should make sure to take your loved ones into account when figuring out which health care plan is for you.</li>
         <li>Am I able to afford health services on my own?&nbsp;Most people are not, which is why they rely on helpful health insurance in order to not pay for these kinds of uncontrollable costs out of pocket.</li>
         <li>Do I have a job that offers me reliable health insurance now?&nbsp;If not, how easy is it for me to obtain reliable health insurance via the health insurance marketplace that the Affordable Care Act has to offer? </li>
         <li>What kind of health coverage will I want in the future?&nbsp;Health care becomes more and more important as we get older and qualify for Medicare.</li>
      </ul><br>
      
